	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Apr 16th 3:58 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=62858><span id= >Tweezle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>15 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The Muddite Recordkeeper conned even at 11, hit for 45 a pop with stun, and hit fast. The Giant Yellowjackets would whomp a level 8 cleric around real good, too.<br><br>You can do this solo at 12 if the fight with the muddite goes well. He stands within view of the exit from Runnyeye. If you pull with a spell, be aware that there is often another muddite standing behind the rock ahead and to your right (as you face the gorge), unseen from the zone-in. Fight the Recordkeeper at the zone and if it goes bad you just step into Runnyeye. Since you are right at the zone line you can probably draft a passing higher level player to help you kill him if necessary.<br><br>If you can't kill the YJs just hang out and someone will shout the /loc of corpses with Pristine Stingers.<br><br>I really like these quests. Good stuff, but No Drop. And they build a sense of community as all the lowbies help each other out with the drops.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Tweezle Lorespinner<br>Gathering of Elders<br>Vazaelle</td></tr>
